<paragraph id="IFRS01_D14"><paranum>D14</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 1"/><data name="paranum" value="D14"/></prolog><body><variant base="F18893862" id="IFRS01_D14_V3"> <p id="IFRS01_P0621">When an entity prepares separate financial statements, <xref base="F77792539" href="../ias27/IAS27_TOC0001.dita#IAS27_TOC0001/IAS27_TOC0001_V3" id="IFRS01_X0770">IAS 27</xref> requires it to account for its investments in subsidiaries, joint ventures and associates either:</p> <ol base="F7283015" id="IFRS01_L0061" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p base="F7283016" id="IFRS01_P0622">at cost;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p base="F7283018" id="IFRS01_P0623">in accordance with <xref base="F67855623" href="../ifrs09/IFRS09_TOC.dita#IFRS09_TOC0001" id="IFRS01_X0771">IFRS 9</xref>; or</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p base="F37046843" id="IFRS01_P0624">using the equity method as described in <xref base="F37046844" href="../ias28/IAS28_TOC.dita#IAS28_TOC0001" id="IFRS01_X0772">IAS 28</xref>.</p></li></ol></variant></body></paragraph>